The paper discusses the impact of data sharing on private cache design in Chip Multiprocessors (CMPs), which falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR). The paper also discusses the effect of cache size on CMP performance, which is related to performance evaluation (cs.PF) and performance modeling (cs.PM). Additionally, the paper discusses the trade-off between cache size and power/resource consumption, which is related to power-aware computing (cs.DC) and system-level design and simulation (cs.SY).
